---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navigation from "../../components/Navigation.astro";
import ContactForm from "../../components/ContactForm.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Work With Us - Medcalf Software Solutions"
  description="Scoped engagements with clear deliverables. Discovery Sprints, Build Sprints, and Advisory retainers for AI, graph database, and automation projects."
>
  <Navigation />

  <main class="services-landing">
    <article class="container">
      <header class="page-header">
        <h1>How We Work Together</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">
          <em>Scoped engagements with clear deliverables</em>
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="page-content">
        <p>
          Every engagement starts with a conversation about what you're trying
          to accomplish. From there, we scope a focused sprint with a defined
          deliverable, timeline, and investment. No ambiguity. No open-ended
          retainers. You know exactly what you're getting.
        </p>

        <section>
          <div class="service-tier">
            <h2>Discovery Sprint</h2>
            <p class="pricing"><strong>$3,500 fixed &bull; 1 week</strong></p>
            <p>
              Not sure if AI, graph databases, or automation is right for your
              problem? Start here. In one week, I'll assess your situation and
              deliver a written recommendation.
            </p>
            <p><strong>You get:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Technical feasibility assessment</li>
              <li>Architecture recommendation with options</li>
              <li>Implementation roadmap with effort estimates</li>
              <li>Go/no-go recommendation with honest reasoning</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              <strong>Best for:</strong> Companies exploring whether AI document processing,
              knowledge graphs, or workflow automation could solve their problem.
            </p>
            <a href="/#contact" class="tier-cta">Book a Discovery Sprint</a>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <div class="service-tier">
            <h2>Build Sprint</h2>
            <p class="pricing">
              <strong>$6,000&ndash;15,000 fixed &bull; 2&ndash;6 weeks</strong>
            </p>
            <p>
              You have a specific problem and you're ready to build. We define
              the scope together upfront, I build it, and you get a working
              system at the end.
            </p>
            <p><strong>You get:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Working prototype, integration, or pipeline</li>
              <li>Documentation and handoff materials</li>
              <li>Weekly progress updates</li>
              <li>2 weeks of bug-fix support after delivery</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              <strong>Best for:</strong> Companies with a defined problem ready for
              a working solution. Often follows a Discovery Sprint.
            </p>
            <a href="/#contact" class="tier-cta">Start a Build Sprint</a>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <div class="service-tier">
            <h2>Advisory</h2>
            <p class="pricing"><strong>$2,000/month ongoing</strong></p>
            <p>
              You need ongoing access to expertise without a specific project.
              I'm available for architecture reviews, technical decisions, and
              strategic guidance.
            </p>
            <p><strong>You get:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>One 60-minute strategy call per month</li>
              <li>Async access via messaging or email (24-48hr response)</li>
              <li>Architecture and code reviews</li>
              <li>Technical decision-making support</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              <strong>Best for:</strong> Teams who've completed a sprint and want
              ongoing guidance, or companies with internal developers who need expert
              oversight on AI/graph implementations.
            </p>
            <a href="/#contact" class="tier-cta">Schedule a Call</a>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="how-it-works">
          <h2>How It Works</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <strong>We talk.</strong> Tell me what you're trying to accomplish.
              No commitment, no pitch.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>I scope it.</strong> If there's a fit, I'll propose a specific
              sprint with deliverables and fixed price.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>I build it.</strong> You get weekly updates and a working result
              at the end.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>You decide what's next.</strong> Another sprint? Advisory retainer?
              Nothing? Your call.
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Recent Work</h2>
          <ul class="recent-work">
            <li>
              <a href="/blog/honey-i-vibe-coded-the-c-suite"
                >Domain-Specific PDF Extraction with ChatGPT</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/blog/StatFoundry-Part1"
                >Modeling the NFL as a Knowledge Graph in Neo4j</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/blog/StatFoundry-Part3"
                >Query Expansion Architecture for Neo4j and React</a
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <ContactForm />
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .services-landing {
    padding-top: 120px;
    padding-bottom: 80px;
    background-color: #fff;
  }

  .services-landing .container {
    max-width: 1000px;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #f0f0f0;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    color: #333;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: #666;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .page-content {
    line-height: 1.8;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .page-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: #444;
  }

  .service-tier {
    background: #f8f9fa;
    border-left: 4px solid #23aa57;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .service-tier h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: #23aa57;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .pricing {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: #333;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .service-tier ul {
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .service-tier li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .how-it-works h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem;
    color: #333;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #23aa57;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .how-it-works ol {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .how-it-works li {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .tier-cta {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    background-color: #23aa57;
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .tier-cta:hover {
    background-color: #1d8f49;
  }

  .page-content > section:last-child h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem;
    color: #333;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #23aa57;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .recent-work {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .recent-work li {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .recent-work a {
    color: #23aa57;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .recent-work a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .services-landing {
      padding-top: 100px;
    }

    .page-header h1 {
      font-size: 2.2rem;
    }

    .subtitle {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    .page-content {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .service-tier h2,
    .how-it-works h2,
    .page-content > section:last-child h2 {
      font-size: 1.6rem;
    }

    .service-tier {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
